A decline in US jobless-benefit rolls to a 28-year low adds to signs of a tight labour market, as initial unemployment claims also remained subdued, Labour Department figures showed Thursday.Highlights of jobless claims (week ended May 6) Key takeawaysThe decline in jobless-benefit rolls dovetails with a drop in the unemployment rate, signaling the labor market continues to strengthen. Initial claims have been below 300 000 since early 2015, rounding out the overall picture of solid economic growth. The continued evidence of a tight labour market is supporting forecasts the Federal Reserve will raise interest rates again next month.Other Details 2017 Bloomberg